{
  "stem": "15768.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He was acquainted with the border guards, and he spirited him out of Germany at night and smuggled him into Belgium.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In Belgium he was arrested because he wasn't a Belgian natural, and he had no papers to be in Belgium.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But I remember years later my father saying it was a pleasure to be in a Belgian jail where everybody was very sympathetic.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was in a small town called Spa, which was directly across the border.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And as it turned out, he had traveled in the business a lot to Holland and Belgium and also France, and he was fluent in French.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It so happened that one of his best customers and finest friends was also living in Spa.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so he not only had personal help there, once he got there, but he also had financial help because knowing the business and so forth these people were very generous in lending money to support us when we went over.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And again, in March of 1939, the same Christian couple spirited us out of the country as well and brought my mother and my brother and myself illegally into Belgium.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, it was interesting.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember we were prepared.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I had never laid eyes on either one of these two people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I wasn't supposed to be able to recognize them, and I had a fairly big mouth [LAUGHS] and also remembered things.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so the first leg was on the train.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And-- Christina--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My mother, my brother, and myself.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
